    <div class="content"><p>Ugh, my DVD player has an automatic detection mode which I can only stop from working if I choose gray bars instead of the less noticeable black bars, and I can't even find a menu that will let me switch it out for DVD's, meaning that whenever I pop in a movie that I really love that isn't widescreen (which for me is basically only Tarkovsky's Stalker, my favourite movie ever looks-wise)  it just ruins it by stretching it as soon as it detects that the input is 4:3</p>
