    <div class="content"><p>The real problem - and what bugs me more than incorrectly set TVs - is that so many people can't even see the distortion even when they're staring at it. Is everyone really unable to tell what a circle should look? Something must be done industry wide so that ALL signals carry a code that tells ALL monitors how they should be displayed, including going into zoom mode for 4x3 letterbox. This is the only solution since we now have ample evidence that putting aspect ratio management in the hands of the end user has been an epic fail.</p>
